# Optional: copy local_keys.example.py to local_keys.py and set DATABASE_URL / DEEPSEEK_API_KEY there
# (same format as Python variables). local_keys.py is gitignored.

# Option A — secrets only on this PC (not inside the project folder):
# 1) Create e.g. C:\Users\YourName\AppData\Local\EasyJob\secrets.env (same KEY=value format as below).
# 2) Set Windows user variable EASYJOB_ENV_FILE to that full path (Environment Variables in System Properties),
#    then open a NEW cmd window. You do not need a .env file inside the repo.
# Option B — file in project folder: copy this file to .env (add .env to .gitignore; never commit it).

DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your_deepseek_api_key_here

# Supabase: Project Settings → Database → copy "URI" (Transaction pooler, port 6543).
# Password characters like @ # % must be URL-encoded in the URI.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@host:6543/postgres

# If connection fails on Windows, try:
# DB_SSL_MODE=prefer

# Optional: comma-separated frontend origins for CORS
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:8000,http://127.0.0.1:8000

# Optional: if /api/quiz/analyze is still used
# QUIZ_ANALYZE_WEBHOOK_URL=
